rassa]]\n| manageryears5  = 1958\u20131959\n| managerclubs5  = [[CE L'Hospitalet|L'Hospitalet]]\n}}\n\n'''Zvonko Monsider''' was a [[Croat]]ian [[football (soccer)|football]] [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]]. He played for both the [[Croatia national football team|Croatian]] and Yugoslavian national teams.\n\nHe started his career with Ferraria Zagreb before moving to [[Concordia Zagreb]] in 1939. He played with Concordia until the establishment of the new regime club [[Dinamo Zagreb]]. Monsider was one of three Concordia players to move to the new club (along with [[Vinko Golob]] and [[Slavko Beda]]).\n\nHe later became a manager with [[CE Sabadell FC|Sabadell]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cesabadell.cat/entrenadors.asp |title=Archived copy |accessdate=11 June 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130510003721/http://www.cesabadell.cat/entrenadors.asp |archivedate=10 May 2013 }}</ref> [[Barakaldo CF]],<ref>http://www.barakaldocf.com/?p=entrenadores</ref> [[UE Sants]], [[Terrassa FC]],<ref>http://hemeroteca.elmundodeportivo.es/preview/1970/07/19/pagina-4/637560/pdf.html?search=monsider</ref> [[CE L'Hospitalet]].<ref>http://www.celh.com/pruebas/historia.asp</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n*[http://www.reprezentacija.rs/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1324 Profile at Serbian federation]\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2010}}\n{{Barakaldo CF managers}}\n{{CE Sabadell FC managers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Monsider, Zvonko}}\n[[Category:1920 births]]\n[[Category:1997 deaths]]\n[[Category:Croatian footballers]]\n[[Category:Croatia international footballers]]\n[[Category:Yugoslav footballers]]\n[[Category:Yugoslavia international footballers]]\n[[Category:Yugoslav First League players]]\n[[Category:H\u0160K Concordia players]]\n[[Category:GNK Dinamo Zagreb players]]\n[[Category:Serie A players]]\n[[Category:S.S. Lazio players]]\n[[Category:Calcio Padova players]]\n[[Category:Uni\u00f3n Magdalena footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Italy]]\n[[Category:Croatian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Dual internationalists (football)]]\n[[Category:Croatian football managers]]\n[[Category:Yugoslav football managers]]\n[[Category:CE Sabadell FC managers]]\n[[Category:Barakaldo CF managers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Zagreb]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:UE Sants managers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Zvonko Monsider\n| fullname   = Zvonimir Monsider\n| image      =\n| birth_date  = 8 January 1920\n| birth_place = [[Zagreb]], [[Kingdom of Yugoslavia]]\n| death_date  = {{death date and age|1997|3|16|1920|1|8|df=yes}}\n| death_place = [[Crystal River, Florida|Crystal River]], [[United States]]\n| height =\n| position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 =\n| years1  = 1938\u20131939 | clubs1  = [[\u0160K Ferraria|Ferraria Zagreb]]    | caps1  = | goals1  = \n| years2  = 1939\u20131945 | clubs2  = [[H\u0160K Concordia|Concordia]]        | caps2  = | goals2  = \n| years3  = 1945\u20131948 | clubs3  = [[NK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]] | caps3  = 19 | goals3  = 0\n| years4  = 1950            | clubs4  = [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]]               | caps4  = 0  | goals4  = 0\n| years5  = 1950            | clubs5  = \u2192 [[Calcio Padova|Padova]] (loan)  | caps5  = 7  | goals5  = 0\n| years6  = 1950            | clubs6  = Hungaria                           | caps6  = | goals6  = \n| years7  = 1951\u20131952 | clubs7  = [[Uni\u00f3n Magdalena|Samarios]]       | caps7  = | goals7  = \n| nationalyears1 = 1942\u20131943 | nationalteam1 = [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]]\n| nationalcaps1  = 6 |nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 1945\u20131947 | nationalteam2 = [[Yugoslavia national football team|Yugoslavia]]\n| nationalcaps2  = 7 |nationalgoals2 = 0\n| manageryears1  = 1953\u20131955  | managerclubs1 = [[CE Sabadell FC|Sabadell]]\n| manageryears2  = 1956\u20131957        | managerclubs2 = [[Barakaldo CF|Barakaldo]]\n| manageryears3  = 1957             | managerclubs3 = [[UE Sants|Sants]]\n| manageryears4  = 1957\u20131958  | managerclubs4 = [[Terrassa FC|Terrassa]]\n| manageryears5  = 1958\u20131959        | managerclubs5 = [[CE L'Hospitalet|L'Hospitalet]]\n}}\n\n'''Zvonko Monsider''' was a [[Croat]]ian [[football (soccer)|football]] [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]]. He played for both the [[Croatia national football team|Croatian]] and Yugoslavian national teams.\n\nHe started his career with Ferraria Zagreb before moving to [[Concordia Zagreb]] in 1939. He played with Concordia until the establishment of the new regime club [[Dinamo Zagreb]]. Monsider was one of three Concordia players to move to the new club (along with [[Vinko Golob]] and [[Slavko Beda]]).\n\nHe later became a manager with [[CE Sabadell FC|Sabadell]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cesabadell.cat/entrenadors.asp |title=Archived copy |accessdate=11 June 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130510003721/http://www.cesabadell.cat/entrenadors.asp |archivedate=10 May 2013 }}</ref> [[Barakaldo CF]],<ref>http://www.barakaldocf.com/?p=entrenadores</ref> [[UE Sants]], [[Terrassa FC]],<ref>http://hemeroteca.elmundodeportivo.es/preview/1970/07/19/pagina-4/637560/pdf.html?search=monsider</ref> [[CE L'Hospitalet]].<ref>http://www.celh.com/pruebas/historia.asp</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n*[http://www.reprezentacija.rs/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1324 Profile at Serbian federation]\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2010}}\n{{Barakaldo CF managers}}\n{{CE Sabadell FC managers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Monsider, Zvonko}}\n[[Category:1920 births]]\n[[Category:1997 deaths]]\n[[Category:Croatian footballers]]\n[[Category:Croatia international footballers]]\n[[Category:Yugoslav footballers]]\n[[Category:Yugoslavia international footballers]]\n[[Category:Yugoslav First League players]]\n[[Category:H\u0160K Concordia playe