er\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|\"Bad Thing\"\n|rowspan=\"3\"|2014\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Kiesza]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"|''[[Sound of a Woman]]''\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|\"The Love\"\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|\"Piano\"\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|\"Praying to a God\"\n|2015\n|[[Nico & Vinz]]\n|''Cornerstone''\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|\"Doubts\"\n|rowspan=\"3\"|2016\n|[[Gorgon City]]\n|''[[Kingdom (Gorgon City album)|Kingdom]]''\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|\"[[Crash (Usher song)|Crash]]\"\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Usher (musician)|Usher]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|''[[Hard II Love]]''\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Co-writer, producer\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|\"[[Rivals (song)|Rivals]]\"\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|\"Helicopters / Beware\"\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2017\n|[[Jidenna]]\n|''[[The Chief (album)|The Chief]]''\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Co-writer\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|\"Can't Wait\"\n|[[dvsn]]\n|''[[Morning After (album)|Morning After]]''\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n*[https://soundcloud.com/saintjhn SAINt JHN on SoundCloud]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jhn, Saint}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American people of Guyanese descent]]\n[[Category:Guyanese musicians]]\n[[Category:American hip hop singers]]\n[[Category:Rappers from Brooklyn]]\n[[Category:21st-century American rappers]]\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n", "name_user": "Ss112", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eStudio albums:updated", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saint_Jhn"}
{"title_page": "Eve Harlow", "text_new": "{{short description|Canadian actress}}\n{{Use Canadian English|date=July 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name = Eve Harlow\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| alt = \n| caption = \n| birth_name = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1989|06|20}}\n| birth_place = [[Moscow]], [[Russian SFSR]], [[USSR]]\n| death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place = \n| death_cause = \n| education = \n| alma_mater = \n| occupation = [[Actress]]\n| years_active = 2007\u2013present\n| spouse = \n| website = <!-- {{URL|www.example.com}} -->\n}}\n\n'''Eve Harlow''' (born June 20, 1989) is a Canadian actress''. ''She is known for her roles on [[television]], including as Maya in the [[The CW|CW]] series [[The 100 (TV series)|''The 100'']] (2014\u20132015), as Taylor in the [[NBC]] [[miniseries]] [[Heroes Reborn (miniseries)|''Heroes Reborn'']] (2015), and as Tess in the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] series ''[[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.]]'' (2017\u20132018). She won a [[Leo Awards|Leo Award]] and received a [[Gemini Awards|Gemini Award]] nomination for her portrayal of Tina Renwald in [[The Guard (Canadian TV series)|''The Guard'']] (2008\u20132009).\n\n== Early life ==\nHarlow is of mixed race,{{fact|date=April 2019}} Jewish ancestry. At seven years old, she moved to [[Canada]].<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Career==\nBeginning in 2007, Harlow began to play small roles in various [[short film]]s, [[feature film]]s, and [[Television show|television series]]; the first role she booked was a [[Cameo appearance|cameo]] in the [[Academy Awards|Academy Award]]-winning film ''[[Juno (film)|Juno]]'' (2007).<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.guardfans.com/cast_harlow.shtml|title=GuardFans.com \u2013 Eve Harlow|last=AMAP|website=www.guardfans.com|access-date=2018-01-12}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, Harlow was cast as Tina Renwald in a Canadian television series ''[[The Guard (Canadian TV series)|The Guard]]''.<ref name=\":0\" /> For this role, Harlow won a [[Leo Award]] for Best Supporting Performance by a Female in a Dramatic Series in 2009,<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.leoawards.com/2009/winners_2009.html|title=Leo Awards, 2009 Winners|website=www.leoawards.com|language=en|access-date=2018-01-12}}</ref> and was nominated for [[Gemini Award]] in 2010.<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com/entertainment/television/2010/08/31/flashpoint_leads_with_15_gemini_nominations.html|title=Flashpoint leads with 15 Gemini nominations|last=Oliveira|first=Michael|date=2010-08-31|work=The Toronto Star|access-date=2018-01-12|language=en-CA|issn=0319-0781}}</ref> Following this, she continued to work steadily on screen, appearing in films, such as ''[[The Tall Man (2012 film)|The Tall Man]]'' (2012),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/celebrity/eve_harlow/|title=Eve Harlow|website=www.rottentomatoes.com|language=en|access-date=2018-01-12}}</ref> and television series, including ''[[Flashpoint (TV series)|Flashpoint]]'' (2011)<ref>{{Citation|last=Fawcett|first=John|title=Good Cop|date=2011-07-15|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1946873/|others=Max Martini, Julian Christopher, Eve Harlow|accessdate=2018-01-12}}</ref> and ''[[Cracked (Canadian TV series)|Cracked]]'' (2013),<ref>{{Citation|last=Donovan|first=Jim|title=Voices|date=2013-11-25|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt3169880/|others=David Sutcliffe, Brooke Nevin, Luisa d'Oliveira|accessdate=2018-01-12}}</ref> among others.\n\nIn 2012, she played a lead role in the short film ''When You Sleep'', directed by [[Ashley McKenzie (director)|Ashley McKenzie]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.nsi-canada.ca/when-you-sleep/|title=When You Sleep {{!}} National Screen Institute \u2013 Canada (NSI)|work=National Screen Institute \u2013 Canada (NSI)|access-date=2018-01-12|language=en-US}}</ref> which won several awards and screened at film festivals around the world, most notably at the [[Cannes Film Festival]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://thechronicleherald.ca/artslife/136150-young-filmmaker-making-her-mark|title=Young filmmaker making her mark|date=2014-04-14|work=The Chronicle Herald|access-date=2018-01-12|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, Harlow played guest roles in several television shows, including ''[[Fargo (TV series)|Fargo]]'', ''[[Bitten (TV series)|Bitten]]'', ''[[The Killing (U.S. TV series)|The Killing]]'', and ''[[Lost Girl (TV series)|Lost Girl]]''.<ref name=\":1\" /> That year, she was also cast as Maya Vie in the [[The 100 (season 2)|second season]] of [[The CW]] show ''[[The 100 (TV series)|The 100]]''.<ref name=\":1\" /> In 2015, Harlow portrayed Taylor Kravid in the [[NBC]] [[miniseries]] ''[[Heroes Reborn (miniseries)|Heroes Reborn]]'', based on the [[Heroes (U.S. TV series)|original series]],<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=http://www.thewrap.com/the-100-alum-eve-harlow-joins-heroes-reborn-event-series-exclusive/|title='The 100' Alum Eve Harlow Joins 'Heroes Reborn' Event Series (Exclusive)|date=2015-04-29|work=TheWrap|access-date=2018-01-12|language=en-US}}</ref> and also appeared in the [[Lifetime (TV network)|Lifetime]] series ''[[UnREAL]]'' as Bethany, the roommate of the main character Rachel Goldberg, portrayed by [[Shiri Appleby]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.tvfanatic.com/2015/06/unreal-season-1-episode-2-review-relapse/|title=UnREAL Season 1 Episode 2 Review: Relapse|date=2015-06-08|work=TV Fanatic|access-date=2018-01-12|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Harlow was cast as Tess, a recurring character in the [[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D. (season 5)|5th season]] of [[Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.|''Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D''.]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://ew.com/tv/2017/11/02/agents-shield-season-5-spoilers-cast/|title=Meet the new season 5 'Agents of S.H.I.E.L.D.' cast members \u2014 first look|work=EW.com|access-date=2018-01-12|language=en}}</ref> and as Melody in the [[Television pilot|pilot]] for the forthcoming [[legal drama]] ''The Jury''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://deadline.com/2016/02/eve-harlow-cast-abc-pilot-the-jury-anthony-carrigan-barry-1201704018/|title=Eve Harlow Joins ABC Pilot \u2018The Jury\u2019; Anthony Carrigan In HBO\u2019s \u2018Barry\u2019|last=Petski|first=Denise|date=2016-02-17|work=Deadline|access-date=2018-01-12|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" |  Notes\n|-\n|2007 \n|''[[Juno (film)|Juno]]'' \n|Tough Girl\n|Cameo{{cn|date=April 2020}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2008 \n|''Sheltered Life''\n|Kendra \n| \n|-\n|''Run Rabbit Run''\n|Nina\n| \n|-\n|rowspan=2|2009 \n|''[[2012 (film)|2012]]'' \n|Cashier \n|\n|-\n|''[[Jennifer's Body (film)|Jennifer's Body]]'' \n|Chloe\n| \n|-\n|2012\n|''[[The Tall Man (2012 film)|The Tall Man]]'' \n|Christine\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2015\n|''[[Lost After Dark]]'' \n|Marilyn\n|\n|- \n|''We're Still Together'' \n|Claire \n|\n|- \n|2018\n|''[[Instant Family]]'' \n|Brenda\n|\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[The Tomorrow Man (film)|The Tomorrow Man]]''\n| Tina\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2007 \n|''My Name Is Sarah''\n|Lola \n|Television film\n|-\n|''[[Kyle XY]]'' \n|Customer #2 \n|Episode: \"[[List of Kyle XY episodes#ep20|House of Cards]]\"\n|-\n|2008 \n|''[[The Andromeda Strain (miniseries)|The Andromeda Strain]]'' \n|Leila \n|Miniseries, 2 episodes\n|-\n|2008\u20132009\n|''[[The Guard (TV series)|The Guard]]'' \n|Tina Renwald \n|Recurring role; 12 episodes\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2009 \n|''Living Out Loud'' \n|Jenny Skinner \n|Television film\n|-\n|''The Farm'' \n|Coco Medina \n|Television film\n|-\n|rowspan=3|2010\n|''[[Fringe (TV series)|Fringe]]''\n|Cashier\n|2 episodes (1 uncredited{{cn|date=April 2020}})\n|-\n|''[[Caprica (TV series)|Caprica]]'' \n|Byun \n|Episode: \"There Is Another Sky\"\n|-\n|''[[Shattered (2010 TV series)|Shattered]